<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.24/8–2346: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Pawley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-23T20:00:00-03:00">August 23, 1946—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1495. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 1959, August 3, noon.<note n="41" xml:id="d115fn41">Not printed.</note> I have approached
                            Ambassador Gracie twice with reference 60,000 passenger car tires and
                            12,000 truck tires. Will see him again today on this subject. Believe it
                            undesirable this time to suggest Argentine Ambassador here approach
                            Foreign Office because Brazilian Foreign Office very much upset with
                            Argentine Govt regarding Argentina’s failure to fulfill its commitment
                            with reference delivery of wheat.</p>
                        <p>(<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 1065, August 8, 8 p.m.).</p>
                        <p>Sent to Buenos Aires; repeated to Dept.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Pawley</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>